301000) form, create a bill, and select the ''SQUEEZO'' vendor in the Summary area. #On the '''Document Details''' tab, click '''Add Row''' on the table toolbar, and add a row with the following settings: #On the form, create a bill with the following settings: #*'''Inventory ID''': ''INSTALL'' #* '''Quantity''': <tt>4.00</tt> #*'''Project''': ''HMBAKERY2'' #* '''Project Task''': ''PHASE1'' #:Notice that the system has selected ''54200 - Project Subcontract Expense'' as the '''Account''' of the bill line, because this is the expense account of the selected item. #In the Summary area, clear the '''Hold''' check box; on the form toolbar, click '''Release''' to release the bill. #On the '''Financial Details''' tab, click the link in the '''Batch Nbr.''' box (and notice this number) to open the batch of general ledger transactions that was created on release of the bill. #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\GL_30_10_00|Journal Transactions] ([~/?ScreenId=GL301000|GL301000]) form, which the system has opened in a pop-up window, review the general ledger transactions that correspond to the released bill. #Close the pop-up window. #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_40_10_00|Project Transaction Details] ([~/?ScreenId=PM401000|PM401000]) form, in the Summary area, select ''HMBAKERY2'' as the '''Project''', and review the project transaction that has been created based on the released accounts payable bill. In the '''GL Batch Nbr.''' column, notice the number of the corresponding batch of general ledger transactions, which is the batch you have just reviewed. #On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\PM_30_10_00|Projects] form, open the ''HMBAKERY2'' project. Review the cost budget on the '''Cost Budget''' tab, and notice how the released bill has affected the '''Actual Quantity''' and '''Actual Amount''' of the corresponding budget line, as shown in the following screenshot. [anchor|#_4fb68384-e002-4a22-b227-cddbe5513dac][anchor|#_4ad7563b-7bbb-4ad1-8865-cd6ce4bad453][image:UserGuide/Image